<title>SOUTH KOREA: LG SEMICON BLAMES PRICES FOR PROFIT FALL.</title>
<headline>LG SEMICON BLAMES PRICES FOR PROFIT FALL.</headline>
<dateline>SEOUL 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>LG Semicon, an affiliate of South Korea's LG Group, said on Thursday falling memory chip prices had caused a sharp fall in its net profit for the first half of calendar 1997.</p>
<p>The company said its official six-month net profit fell to 16 billion won from 131.4 billion won a year earlier.</p>
<p>LG had earlier projected a first-half profit of 30 billion won.</p>
<p>An official said the earlier estimate was based on a 16-megabit DRAM (dynamic random access memory) chip price of about $7 in June but the price fell to the $6 level.</p>
